Bayesian Networks

Introduction
A Bayesian Network is a probabilistic graphical model representing random variables and their dependencies.

Example Problem

Predict whether a person will travel based on:
1. Weather
2. Budget

Network Structure
Weather -> Travel
Budget -> Travel

Variables:
Weather: Good, Bad
Budget: High, Low
Travel: Yes, No
Conditional Probability Table
Weather -	Budget - P(Travel)
Good - High	- 0.95
Good - Low - 0.75
Bad - High - 0.50
Bad - Low - 0.10

Inference:
Using probability rules, the network computes the probability that a person will travel.

Result:
P(Travel) ≈ 0.697

